      • isSameValueTypeAs

        public boolean isSameValueTypeAs​(Value value)
        Description copied from class: Value
        Returns whether or not the type of this value is the same as the type of the given value. Value type is more specific than what Value.valueGroup() returns, but less granular than, say specific class. For example there are specific classes for representing string values for various scenarios, but they're all strings... same type.
        Overrides:
        isSameValueTypeAs in class Value
        Parameters:
        value - Value to compare type against.
        Returns:
        true if the given value is of the same value type as this value.
